<kml xmlns="http://www.opengis.net/kml/2.2">
<Document>
<name>Skyline Drive</name>
<description><![CDATA[<h2>Skyline Drive</h2><p><i>Virginia, USA · Shenandoah National Park, Front Royal to Rockfish Gap</i></p><p><b>169 km of pure ridgeline, 75 overlooks, the older sibling of the Blue Ridge Parkway.</b></p><table style='font-family:sans-serif'><tr><td><b>Approx. length:</b></td><td>113 km (70 mi)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Drive time:</b></td><td>4–5 hrs</td></tr><tr><td><b>Best season:</b></td><td>May (wildflowers), mid-Oct (foliage — but expect heavy crowds)</td></tr><tr><td><b>Watch out for:</b></td><td>Deer (extreme), bears, slow traffic, fog, ice in winter, 56 km/h speed limit strictly enforced</td></tr><tr><td><b>Track points:</b></td><td>199</td></tr></table><hr><p>75 overlooks in 105 miles, max 35 mph (56 km/h), built 1933–39 by the Civilian Conservation Corps as a Depression-era project. The whole road sits on the spine of the Blue Ridge with the Shenandoah Valley to the west and the Piedmont to the east. Black bears are more abundant here than anywhere else east of the Mississippi. Connects directly to the Blue Ridge Parkway at Rockfish Gap on its south end — two parks, 924 km, in one near-continuous ridge drive.</p><h3>Scenic points marked on this route:</h3><ul><li><b>Hogback overlook</b> — Longest panorama of the Shenandoah River bends — fall sunrise here is famous.</li><li><b>Skyland</b> — Highest accommodations on the drive, established 1894. Limberlost Trail (1 km, accessible) loops through old-growth hemlock.</li><li><b>Hawksbill Mountain</b> — Highest peak in the park (1,235 m). 4 km loop hike from Hawksbill Gap with the best 360° view in Shenandoah.</li><li><b>Big Meadows</b> — Rare high-elevation meadow maintained by mowing and prescribed fire. Visitor center, lodge, abundant deer at dawn/dusk.</li></ul><hr><p><i>Track geometry is interpolated between named waypoints — use a routing service to snap to actual road for navigation. Waypoints, scenic POIs, and notes are reliable.</i></p>]]></description>
